15:02.047 --> 15:03.402
<i>I still can't stand him.</i>

15:03.577 --> 15:04.940
<i>I still can't stand him.</i>

15:05.105 --> 15:05.853
<i>I still can't stand him.</i>

15:05.968 --> 15:07.603
I don't care
about these church jerks.

15:07.858 --> 15:10.430
<i>Church jerks... church jerks...</i>

15:10.995 --> 15:13.213
Homer, your behavior is heinous.

15:13.288 --> 15:14.403
Anus, anus...

15:14.496 --> 15:16.211
anus, anus, anus...

15:16.607 --> 15:18.803
Stupid Sideshow Bob.

15:18.898 --> 15:20.661
Even when he's dead,
he wrecks my life.

15:20.836 --> 15:22.713
I hope he's in hell
eating a barf burger.

15:22.966 --> 15:24.693
I once felt that way, too.

15:24.897 --> 15:26.312
Hey, aren't you Bob's brother?

15:26.445 --> 15:27.633
Biologically, yes,

15:27.638 --> 15:28.833
but we never got along.

15:29.056 --> 15:30.871
He was always
zigging when I zagged.

15:31.158 --> 15:33.173
That summer when he wanted to tour
the castles of Italy,

15:33.288 --> 15:34.863
I wanted to tour
the castles of France.

15:35.076 --> 15:36.321
So we went to Spain,

15:36.326 --> 15:37.563
a compromise that satisfied no one.

15:37.768 --> 15:38.703
That's stupid.

15:38.958 --> 15:40.661
You talk like youre smart,
but you're stupid.

15:40.865 --> 15:43.583
Anyway, I choose to remember
Bob as the big brother

15:43.698 --> 15:45.311
who taught me to play Botticelli.

15:45.576 --> 15:46.362
Sounds boring.

15:46.467 --> 15:47.501
Oh, you'd love it.

15:47.738 --> 15:49.313
It's a guessing game
in which one

15:49.386 --> 15:51.363
player adopts the guise
of a noteworthy--

15:51.595 --> 15:53.090
you're right, it is boring.

15:54.247 --> 15:55.822
But the only way
you'll find happiness

15:56.017 --> 15:57.572
is by making your peace with Bob.

15:57.746 --> 16:00.141
Well, I guess I could say good-bye.

16:00.215 --> 16:01.181
You'd better make it snappy.

16:01.386 --> 16:02.850
They're cremating him in 30 minutes.

16:02.937 --> 16:05.523
I'll be scattering his ashes
over the castles of France.

16:07.137 --> 16:08.491
Take that, ashes.

16:13.608 --> 16:16.300
Hey, Bart! You're on the
front page of the paper.

16:17.138 --> 16:19.502
I'm going to set things right.
Wanna come with me?

16:19.677 --> 16:22.521
I would, but tonight my dad's
taking me to the batting cage.

16:22.695 --> 16:24.750
He's gonna teach me to umpire!

16:24.965 --> 16:26.493
Check it out, an official

16:26.496 --> 16:28.030
Major Leagueball/strike counter!

16:28.276 --> 16:31.500
Ball one, ball two, strike one...

16:32.227 --> 16:33.993
Bart? Bart?

16:41.147 --> 16:42.340
Hi, Lisa.

16:42.538 --> 16:44.170
Hate to mix"B" with "P,"

16:44.298 --> 16:46.450
but your family owes
me for two weeks.

16:46.686 --> 16:48.243
Milhouse, have you seen Bart?

16:48.468 --> 16:49.510
Bart Simpson?

16:49.657 --> 16:51.033
I think he went to pay his

16:51.035 --> 16:52.413
respects to Sideshow Bob.

16:52.736 --> 16:54.563
Mind if I sit down for a second?

16:54.717 --> 16:56.270
My feet are killing me.

16:56.988 --> 16:58.713
Feet... killing?!

16:59.608 --> 17:00.743
We've got to save Bart!

17:00.956 --> 17:02.821
Now?
But I'm getting a home perm.

17:02.957 --> 17:03.692
Now!

17:10.048 --> 17:11.701
Bob, it's me, Bart.

17:11.885 --> 17:14.531
I came here to tell you
I never meant for you to die.

17:14.708 --> 17:17.262
I just wanted you to go to jail
and get beat up a lot.

17:17.548 --> 17:19.483
Now everyone wishes I was dead.

17:19.887 --> 17:22.931
Then let's give the people
what they want!

17:24.165 --> 17:25.252
Sideshow Bob!

17:44.326 --> 17:45.953
Bob planned this
from the beginning.

17:46.055 --> 17:47.613
He wanted to be captured
at the restaurant.

17:47.995 --> 17:49.493
He would never get
a Shakespeare quote wrong.

17:49.578 --> 17:50.070
No.

17:50.257 --> 17:51.701
His mother was a Shakespearian actress.

17:52.555 --> 17:54.323
- His father is a doctor.
- A doctor, huh?

17:54.488 --> 17:56.462
So when Bob collapsed in the courtroom...

17:56.468 --> 17:56.991
I remember.

17:57.156 --> 17:58.642
...his father could take that

17:58.648 --> 17:59.922
opportunity to inject Bob

18:00.047 --> 18:02.682
with a powerful drug
that simulated death.

18:03.196 --> 18:05.230
It was a diabolical scheme, and every

18:05.236 --> 18:07.160
member of his family played a part!

18:07.445 --> 18:09.450
Are you done? 'Cause I've been
circling the funeral home

18:09.577 --> 18:10.752
- for ten minutes.
- Yes.

18:14.795 --> 18:17.802
Cool, I found a trapdoor that
leads to an underground city.

18:18.537 --> 18:19.920
Here I go!

18:24.556 --> 18:27.252
Oh, my God, it's beautiful!

18:27.546 --> 18:29.363
- Are you buying this?
- When they find your ashes,

18:29.475 --> 18:31.041
they'll think it's me.

18:31.245 --> 18:33.950
And I'll be far away
with my loving family.

18:34.187 --> 18:35.881
It's the perfect crime.

18:36.065 --> 18:37.891
And it was my flawless performance

18:38.026 --> 18:40.280
as the grieving brother
that sealed the deal.

18:40.446 --> 18:43.190
Yes, and Hamlet is all about Laertes.

18:43.406 --> 18:46.410
Would you please stop
comparing me to Laertes!

18:46.598 --> 18:48.571
If the doublet fits...

18:54.328 --> 18:56.021
Stop that cremation!

18:56.698 --> 18:58.391
Hey, what smells so good?

18:58.597 --> 19:00.573
Zeus' pimples!

19:04.085 --> 19:06.032
Hot! Hot! Hot!

19:06.328 --> 19:08.450
You're too late, Simpsons!

19:08.665 --> 19:10.181
Eat hobo remains!

19:12.606 --> 19:13.602
Get me out of here!

19:13.786 --> 19:16.202
What are you doing?
I can't breathe!

19:16.338 --> 19:19.482
Marge, he's got to get
over his fear of coffins.

19:22.677 --> 19:24.803
Freeze, Sideshow Snobs!

19:25.786 --> 19:27.023
You're all under arrest.

19:27.257 --> 19:29.723
You have the right to remain silent,
but I hope you don't.

19:30.066 --> 19:32.430
It's a long way to jail
and I like to chitchat.

19:34.746 --> 19:36.062
Wait, I must know.

19:36.267 --> 19:37.933
How did you loosen the tiles

19:37.938 --> 19:39.302
of my mosaic of murder?

19:39.647 --> 19:41.931
I grew suspicious
when I saw the casket

19:42.168 --> 19:44.582
had extra room
built-in for your feet.

19:44.877 --> 19:46.581
Why would your family pay all

19:46.585 --> 19:48.420
that extra money of a dead man?

19:49.475 --> 19:52.413
Damn these glorious gunboats!

19:53.268 --> 19:54.340
Nice try, Bob,

19:54.477 --> 19:56.381
but you didn't count on one thing.

19:56.555 --> 19:59.380
- What's that?
- You stink like my butt!

20:01.127 --> 20:01.903
Take him away!

20:02.338 --> 20:06.313
Oh, why must I feed him
straight lines?!

20:11.198 --> 20:13.822
Well, this time I think Sideshow Bob

20:13.827 --> 20:16.013
is finally locked up for good.

20:16.247 --> 20:17.663
Yeah, the only thing that's

20:17.665 --> 20:19.352
going to be hacked to pieces now

20:19.617 --> 20:21.233
is this celebratory cake!

20:22.968 --> 20:26.153
So who wants a nice big slice?

20:27.017 --> 20:27.831
Slash!

20:27.916 --> 20:29.320
Hack! Die!

20:36.255 --> 20:38.332
There he goes again.

20:38.606 --> 20:40.670
You have 87 years to get
used to it, Father.

20:42.146 --> 20:43.790
East bids two hearts.

20:43.948 --> 20:44.790
Three diamonds.

20:45.066 --> 20:46.131
Three clubs.

20:49.025 --> 20:51.363
The joke's not funny
and the bid's not sufficient.

